snippet.textDisplay:
Since we're all talking about the different experience we had listening to this song! I'll say what happened to me :)
I was scrolling through Facebook and saw the post about this song. Apparently it was just hours in the studio and they wanted to sing it the following Sunday. I thought to myself "it must be pretty good then!"

When I saw that MINUTE AND 50 SECOND preview I said "HOLLLLLUP. THIS IS STRAIGHT BIBLE".

Find it here on Youtube and guess what? NOW I'M CRYING TOO. (Note, I read through all the comments first, then heard it and cried anyways.) When they sung "Amen"...bro... How do I put this? It's like God sang that to me and everyone hearing it. It's like he's saying "It's happening, I'm gonna make it happen". Like I'm not singing this over me and declaring or anything it's just GOD saying "I'M GOING TO DO IT, THIS IS A MANDATE, A COMMAND, AN ORDER" like no ifs, ands, or buts it's happening. Like a flood, nothing can stop it. We're getting this blessing to the face yall. We're gonna see it. Id say it's quite prophetic. And exciting.

snippet.textDisplay: It's been a long time since I last had a goosebump and cried through a worship song. I've not been actively committing myself to my ministry lately bcoz of my school and work excuses.
